\pard\sa200\sl240\slmult1\qc\fs24 T = \f1\lang1042\'d6\sub\f0 e\super t\nosupersub  / \f1\'d6\sub\f0 e\super i\nosupersub  = e^-\f1\lang18\'f4\f0\lang1042  = 10\super -A\nosupersub\fs20\lang18\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl240\slmult1  Above equation of the transmittance T is comparable with the equation which was handled in the optical depth part.\par
 The relation of the attenuation cross section with molar attenuation coefficient is\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl240\slmult1\qc\f1\fs24\lang1042\'e5\sub\f0 i\nosupersub  = \f1\'f3\sub\f0 i \nosupersub N\sub A\nosupersub  / ln(10)\par
\par

\pard\sa200\sl240\slmult1\fs20\lang18 and number density of the attenuating sample and amount conentration is\par
